.TH "cipso_v4_sock_setattr" 9 "cipso_v4_sock_setattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cipso_v4_sock_setattr \- Add a CIPSO option to a socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cipso_v4_sock_setattr
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "const struct cipso_v4_doi *doi_def "  ","
.BI "const struct netlbl_lsm_secattr *secattr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
the socket
.IP "doi_def" 12
the CIPSO DOI to use
.IP "secattr" 12
the specific security attributes of the socket
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the CIPSO option on the given socket using the DOI definition and
security attributes passed to the function.  This function requires
exclusive access to \fIsk\fP, which means it either needs to be in the
process of being created or locked.  Returns zero on success and negative
values on failure.
